<TEXT>
a united airlines jet blew all the tires on its 
right side upon landing thursday on hawaii island but there were 
no injuries among the passengers and crew officials said 
the tires on the left side of the dc8 also were flattened 
during the landing at the keaholekona airport said state 
department of transportation spokeswoman marilyn kali 
the 163 passengers and nine crew members aboard united flight 31 
from san francisco evacuated the plane by stairs after the 1116 
am landing she said and emergency slides were not required 
the airport closed for three hours while pieces of the rubber 
tires were removed from the runway and replacement tires were flown 
in from honolulu so the plane could be moved she said 
united officials said they did not know what caused the 
blowouts rob doughty a spokesman at united headquarters in 
chicago said mechanics would fly from honolulu to check the plane 
a larger plane friday would accomodate passengers unable to make 
their connecting flights thursday he said 
doughty said the aircraft would be retired this fall along with 
the rest of uniteds dc8 fleet 
</TEXT>
