the airlift and convoy are part of the united nations operation 
lifelife sudan meant to stock more than 110000 tons of food and 
supplies in wartorn southern sudan before heavy seasonal rains 
begin in midmay 
the 132 million operation aims to prevent a repeat of 1988s 
tragedy when between 250000 and 500000 people died because of a 
famine caused by drought floods and the 6yearold insurgency by 
the sudan peoples liberation army 
a giant c130 hercules cargo plane carrying 155 tons of maize 
landed in torit after leaving ugandas entebbe airport before dawn 
