the plane leased from and operated by the miamibased southern 
air transport co is to make three flights daily to torit until it 
has delivered 1100 tons he said 
mitchell said todays delivery was the first large shipment of 
relief food to the town the norwegian peoples aid and world 
vision relief agencies have delivered 100 tons of food to torit 
since april 1 he said 
gote hertz a un spokesman in kampala said a 47truck convoy 
carrying 1100 tons of food also started off today he said the 
convoy first will deliver food to the sudanese border town of 
nimule then travel 60 miles northeast to torit if the convoy 
leaders believe conditions are safe 
in recent weeks torits civilian population has swelled from 
3000 to 25000 as displaced southerners seeking food and shelter 
pour in from the surrounding bush un officials expect the 
population to climb to 50000 in the coming weeks 
on tuesday the first un convoy in rebelheld southern sudan 
was ambushed as it traveled west to torit from the sudan peoples 
liberation base of kapoeta eight rebel escorts were killed and 
the convoys lead truck was destroyed un officials have not 
assessed blame for the attack 
operation lifeline began april 1 after the united nations 
