disappearance than the passersby who crowded around the pond this 
week 
the loss of ducklings is always unfortunate but it is not 
abnormal to lose 50 percent of a brood in the wild said mike 
smith a spokesman for the us fish and wildlife service 
freshly hatched ducklings are extremely vulnerable and very easy 
targets for predators 
said ms horton 
animals have more offspring than can possibly survive and 
once they die they provide a valuable source of food for other 
animals its all part of the natural order of things 
it happens all the time in the wilderness but its hard for 
people right here in the city to watch nature doing its thing 
