all you need for the annual louisiana jazz 
and heritage festival is a good set of ears some comfortable 
clothes and lots of napkins to wipe the grease from your lips 
the festival launches its 20th anniversary this month with a 
twoweek 3 million celebration featuring 3000 musicians and tons 
of good food 
i honestly think the new orleans festival is not only the 
largest but the most important in the world said george wein 
the producer who founded the new orleans event and helped launch 
others including the famed newport jazz festival 
lots of big name artists come to the jazz fest and hide 
themselves in the crowd so they can enjoy it 
the formula for success has been finetuned since that first 
1969 festival in congo square off rampart street and this years 
event scheduled april 28 through may 7 will look a lot like the 
one last year 
its been so successful that we didnt see any reason to 
change it said anna zimmerman spokeswoman for the festival 
were always looking for ways to make things work better but 
we looked into the archives about when it started and its 
basically the same its just bigger were expecting 300000 
and well be happy with that 
the festival is really two events a series of evening jazz 
concerts and a pair of weekend heritage fairs with openair stages 
surrounded by food and crafts 
this years concerts feature wynton marsalis miles davis 
george benson jimmy buffett al green and santana 
