creative thinkers needed for the future 
some critics say no 
korean education like the system in neighboring japan is based 
on rote memorization that enables a student who works hard to 
produce enormous amounts of facts and data that result in 
impressive scores on tests designed for such a regimen 
in south korea education is equated with success the argument 
goes the more education the more success the more people 
educated the greater success for the nation 
detractors say the system clones human computers who can pour 
out endless streams of information but cannot think creatively and 
that it contributes to the insecurity and tension that beset south 
korean society 
the american manager of a company in seoul said he hired a dozen 
