march period amounted to 103 million down 62 percent from 273 
million in the same quarter a year ago 
sales in the quarter were up 5 percent to 4 billion from 38 
billion in 1988 
without the buyoutrelated costs and a charge for abandoning the 
premier tests net income would have been up 17 percent to 320 
