soybean futures prices closed sharply higher and 
grain futures also advanced friday on the chicago board of trade as 
the weather outlook turned drier for the midwest and great plains 
soybean futures also were supported by the slow movement of 
brazilian soybean meal to europe a function of a 12dayold 
dockworkers strike at the port of santos brazils largest harbor 
but weather was the dominant factor and it is certain to remain 
the key variable in the markets with corn planting expected to 
begin in earnest this weekend in the midwest 
