planting commences in several more weeks 
soybeans need more moisture to get started than corn does 
said walter spilka a grain market analyst with smith barney 
harris upham amp co in new york when you see dry forecasts 
youre likely to see a better runup in the soybean market 
predictions for continued dry weather in the great plains 
bolstered wheat prices the kansas wheat crop has already sustained 
significant dryweather damage and without rain theres no doubt 
the crop will continue to deteriorate spilka said 
