<TEXT>
the procter amp gamble co hopes its move to use 
recycled plastic in some of its products sets an example for the 
rest of the industry 
the cincinnatibased company announced thursday it is test 
marketing four of its major liquid laundry and cleaning products in 
bottles partially made of recycled plastic 
pampgs message is that plastics are recyclable too and should 
be added to all recycling programs said company spokesman t 
scott stewart we want to promote development of a nationwide 
program to collect process and recycle plastics in consumer 
packaging 
the company is test marketing its liquid tide and cheer laundry 
detergents downy fabric softner and spic and span household 
cleaner in bottles containing 20 percent to 30 percent recycled 
plastic the bottles are being test marketed in the states of 
washington oregon and montana 
all four products are being rolled out now toward the 
northwest stewart said 
not only is the northwest farthest in distance it also 
represents informed areas relative to recycling seattle has a 
curbside program in which paper glass and aluminum are collected 
separate from the trash he said 
successful testmarketing of the bottles eventually could mean 
the substitution of 20 million to 30 million pounds of new plastic 
and recycled material annually according to pampg the company hopes 
it is the beginning of a major effort by companies to increase the 
use of recycled plastics 
pampg said it has been working with various companies to produce 
the recycled plastic bottles the inner layers of all the bottles 
are made of new plastic and the outer layers are made with a 
combination of new and recycled plastic 
the bottles being used in the market test arent specially 
marked to note their recycled content the initial shipments are 
aimed at finding out whether the special bottles hold up to regular 
wear and tear during shipping stewart said 
the project wont necessarily provide a savings or marketing 
advantage according to tom rattray pampgs associate director for 
corporate packing development 
deborah anderson the companys director of environmental 
coordination said procter amp gamble hopes to develop a way to use 
highdensity polyethylene the soft flexible plastic used for 
milk juice detergent and other bottles from any source 
including its own detergent bottles 
procter amp gamble had worldwide sales of 193 billion during 
fiscal 198788 its businesses include laundry and cleaning 
products pharmaceuticals and food and beverage products 
