<TEXT>
corporate researchers are discovering that 
proper support for the buttocks can improve the bottom line 
at the research complex of furniture maker herman miller inc 
engineers and technicians say comfy and supportive seats are 
crucial in a country where 70 percent to 80 percent of workers have 
sedentary jobs many hunched over computers for long periods 
studies have shown that productivity increases when 
ergonomic seating is introduced said neil goldberg a company 
researcher if people are comfortable and have the support they 
need they will tend to sit longer and work longer 
herman miller the worlds secondlargest office furniture maker 
behind steelcase inc of grand rapids this week introduced two new 
chair designs and invited reporters for a lesson in ergonomics 
the science of adapting working conditions to suit workers 
the company sells comfort with statistics it says absence from 
work due to back pain has increased 40 percent since 1970 while a 
total of about 5 billion is paid out annually to employees by 
insurance companies for back and neck pain claims 
when sitting about 75 percent of a persons total body weight 
is supported on four square inches of the buttocks sitting on a 
hard flat surface can put pressure of 85 pounds to 100 pounds per 
square inch on the buttocks which can restrict blood flow herman 
miller says 
the company said about 38 percent of workers who sit in front of 
computers most of the day experience back pain 
independent research confirms much of herman millers sales 
pitch 
you cant just buy an office chair as an afterthought said 
marvin dainoff a psychology professor at miami universitys center 
for ergonomic research in oxford ohio who has studied work 
environments 
if you focus on the employees daily work and get a chair that 
fits you will see a difference in productivity he said 
in studies he performed in 198182 dainoff had 12 temporary 
clerical workers conduct dataentry work at a typical work 
station with a standard desk governmentissue secretarial chair 
and a computer terminal with attached keyboard under a bank of 
fluorescent lights 
the workers would rotate between that environment and an 
optimal one with good lighting an ergonomic chair and work 
station adjustable keyboard and antiglare monitor 
measuring key stroke and error rates dainoff found an average 
247 percent increase in productivity with the workers at the 
optimal work station in a second study the only variable was the 
office furniture and dainoff found a 17 percent productivity 
increase 
goldberg said comfort selfadjusting support and the matching 
of the seat to the workers task are the most important factors in 
selecting an office chair the way to minimize the stress of a 
static posture is to have a chair that allows the worker to move 
tilt pivot recline and stretch 
a good chair becomes invisible you forget youre sitting 
goldberg said if youre uncomfortable sitting is all you think 
about 
but a good seat doesnt come cheap herman millers stressfree 
productionenhancing midpriced office chairs list for between 
450 and 800 
</TEXT>
