airs on sundays 
as part of that project the schools get a 40page classroom 
guide via computer with tips on how the show can be used to 
complement lessons in science social studies mathematics 
language or the arts 
one of the differences between the services however is that 
whittle is providing about 50000 in television sets video 
recorders and satellite dishes to each of the participating schools 
while the schools subscribing to news access must provide their own 
equipment 
another is that whittle requires that schools air its daily news 
program to the entire student body each school day while teachers 
using the weekly news access program are free to use segments in 
class and are not bound to show any of it to their students 
