<TEXT>
the venerable new york stock exchange long a 
bastion of resistance to the global push toward 24hour securities 
trading said friday it is studying ways of developing a system of 
offhours transactions 
the admission by the 198yearold big board was viewed as a 
reaction to moves by competing stock exchanges to implement fully 
computerized roundtheclock trading systems that could siphon away 
business from wall street 
under computerized trading shares of stock can be traded 
electronically when the exchange floor is shut down via programs 
that automatically match up buyers and sellers for various 
securities 
nyse spokesman richard torrenzano said the exchange plans to 
discuss the issue with customers traders institutional investors 
listed companies and securities firms 
what were saying is in the next six to 24 months well be 
looking at a number of different things torrenzano said 
were not sure there is enough demand to make the nyse go to 
24hour trading he said we have to go out and talk to all the 
various parties in the market based on those needs and demands 
the new york stock exchange will be very responsive and committed 
the tiny cincinnati stock exchange last month announced plans to 
implement computerized 24hour trading in the next 19 months more 
perilous for the nyse chicagos two futures markets announced they 
are developing afterhours trading systems 
overseas the toronto stock exchange the tokyo stock exchange 
and other markets have introduced at least partially automated 
execution systems and have been open to the concept of harnessing 
technology to give investors the option of buying or selling at any 
time 
im afraid its possible that us equities markets could move 
to another marketplace domestically or even to another marketplace 
offshore in the event of a better system said junius w peake 
chairman of peakeryerson consulting group inc an international 
capital markets firm its still the better mousetrap theory 
it doesnt matter if youre in tokyo or bermuda or rio de 
janeiro i dont care where the location of the transaction occurs 
as long as i know its a good trade 
the new york stock exchange where an average of 160 million 
shares of the listed 1680 stocks change hands daily has resisted 
automation in part wall street officials say because of pressure 
from floor brokers and firms not to tamper with the system 
in todays nyse an electronic delivery system routes orders to 
the exchange floor where they are handled by professional market 
makers called specialists who shout out buy and sell orders in the 
manner of an auction 
these middlemen would be dinosaurs in a fully automated 
enviroment and unnecessary in offhours trading when a computer 
system would match up buyers and sellers of a desired stock at any 
time of day or night 
one criticism of 24hour electronic trading is that without 
specialists to take the other side of the trade orders will hang 
in limbo until an opposing order arrives 
under the globex tradematching system developed by the chicago 
mercantile exchange and the british firm reuters holdings plc the 
number of orders best bids and offers and quantity of bids and 
offers will be listed immediately on a computer screen 
another offhours trading system known as aurora planned by 
the chicago board of trade will simulate the chaotic commodities 
trading pits on a computer screen 
new york stock exchange chairman john phelan received a 
presentation by the developers of the chicago merc system last week 
but was absolutely noncommittal about whether the exchange 
would adopt new technology a participant said 
the nyse maintains that it does not feel threatened by the 
infusion of automatic trading 
torrenzano said the nyse studied offhours trading in 1984 and 
1985 and found little demand the nyse the worlds secondlargest 
exchange behind tokyo in september 1985 expanded trading time by 
a half hour daily and is now open from 930 am to 4 pm 
i think were living in a much more competitive environment 
but i dont think thats causing us to take a closer look he 
said to take a leadership position in the equities marketplace 
today you must be looking at what everyones doing all the time 
