chrysler corp on friday announced separate 
recalls of some 198788 jeep wrangler and 1989 dodge raider 
sportutility vehicles 
chrysler said in a statement that it would replace windshield 
wiper linkage components and install a reinforcement to the 
windshield frame on about 80000 jeep wranglers the repairs were 
needed to prevent potential cracking of the windshield frame at the 
wiper pivot mountings which in turn could cause dislocation of the 
wiper linkage the statement said 
chrysler also said it would install a heat adaptor plate below 
the throttle body on about 4600 dodge raiders equipped with 
3liter sixcylinder engines the repairs would prevent ice 
formation on the throttle body blade in temperatures below 10 
degrees a condition that could prevent the throttle from returning 
to the idle position when the accelerator pedal is released the 
statement said 
owners were being asked to return the vehicles to dealers for 
free repairs chrysler said the automaker said it was not aware of 
accidents or injuries resulting from either problem 
